This paper focuses on trajectory planning for autonomous driving, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a hierarchical planning approach that involves optimization, which is a common technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of simulations and real tests, which suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also involves optimization techniques, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
